hance to survive and even reverse the process if they have someone to talk to them regularly and for a sustained period, soon after their first breakdown.    In this sensitive and evocative narrative, he draws on his personal experiences working with schizophrenics since the 1960's. He offers his interpretation of how schizophrenia develops, typically in the teens, as an adaptation in the difficult transition to adulthood.  With tenderness, Bollas depicts schizophrenia as an understandable way of responding to our precariousness in a highly unpredictable world.  He celebrates the courage of the children he has worked with and reminds us that the wisdom inherent in human beings-to turn to conversation with others when in distress-is the fundamental foundation of any cure for human conflict.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Feb 2020) 0aPsychoanalysis. 0aPsychosesxTreatment. 0aSchizophreniaxTreatment. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Psychopathology / Schizophrenia.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2014-2015z978311067250340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300216233423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300216233.jpg  a978-3-11-067250-3  YUP eBook Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aEBA_FAO